        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17852",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that the proper solution is, as you suggested, to implement the assertion method... however you want, including assertion chains. This is actually quite trivial to do, and I don't see a compelling need to bloat the API with this. If you disagree, please feel free to reopen the issue with more feedback. Thank you! :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-10T12:30:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-10T12:30:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17867",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=marcis",
                        "name": "marcis",
                        "displayName": "Marcos Gil Fuertes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "OK, thanks. \n\nI was implementing a new class (calling multiple asserts) for each combination of asserts in the application. Now, I realized it can be done by implementing a generic 'MultiAssert' class like this:\n\n{code} \nclass MultiAssert implements Zend_Acl_Assert_Interface {\n\n    protected $_asserts;\n\n    public function __construct(array $asserts) {\n        foreach ($asserts as $assert) {\n            Zend_Loader::autoload($assert);\n            $this->_asserts[] = new $assert();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public function assert(Zend_Acl $acl, Zend_Acl_Role_Interface $role = null,\n                           Zend_Acl_Resource_Interface $resource = null, $privilege = null) {\n        $result = TRUE;\n        foreach ($this->_asserts as $assert) {\n            $result &= $assert->assert($acl, $role, $resource, $privilege);\n        }\n        return $result ;\n    }\n}\n{code} ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=marcis",
                        "name": "marcis",
                        "displayName": "Marcos Gil Fuertes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-12T06:35:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-12T06:35:59.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
